  "abstractText": [
    "In this essay we explain how the aim to overcome the corona crisis through togetherness is impeded by three counterproductive bordering tendencies: utilitarian locking up, nationalistic locking in and exclusionary locking out. We argue that this ongoing geopolitical b/ordering and othering of people along the lines of age, gender, nationality or ethnicity, what we together coin coronativism, falls short in dealing with the crisis in an effective as well as non‐discriminatory manner, and could even have autoimmune effects in terms of global health as well as in terms of democracy and rule of law. To effectively combat the crisis, we make a plea for the employment of a different conceptualisation of solidarity, a radical non‐dividing form of togetherness,beyond nativistic divides: agape."
  ],
